                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Tender raises hopes for Bengal infotech
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, May 8: A tender for an underwater cable between India and Southeast Asia, the landing station for which will be at Digha, was floated today.        
	To carry data for the IT industry, this cable is a project of Millennium Telecom, a joint venture between state-run Mahanagar Telephone Nigam Limited and Bharat Sanchar Nigam Limited. The tender is worth Rs 1,600 crore.        
	In a communication to the department of telecommunications, Bengal IT minister Debesh Das had said, It was a long felt need for eastern India, considering the vast potential of this region in software and IT-enabled services sector.         
	The West Bengal government has set a target of contributing about 15 per cent to the countrys total revenue earnings from IT export by 2010. It also aims to create an additional 200,000 jobs in the sector by 2010.        
	West Bengal has more than 250 companies registered under the software technology parks of India scheme and currently employs some 50,000 software professionals.        
	With many leading IT and BPO firms setting up shop in the state, the landing station will further boost the sector.         
	Recently, Infosys Technologies had announced an investment of Rs 500 crore in West Bengal. Other firms that are keen to extend their footprint in the state are back-office firm IBM Daksh and software firms Accenture, HCL Technologies, Cognizant and Genpact. Accentures Calcutta centre would be its largest in Asia.        
	Convergys, HCL Infotech and Patni are also in talks with the state government for setting up centres in Calcutta.                                                                                                                                      
